</i></p><p class="sc-dtMgUX eyUPwo pf-14_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">In the dynamic landscape of dental care, continuous professional development (CPD) stands as a cornerstone for maintaining excellence and ensuring patient safety. Enhanced CPD represents a refined approach, tailored to meet the evolving demands of modern dental practice. In this blog, Dr Richard Dune delves into the intricacies of enhanced CPD, exploring its significance, regulatory framework, and best practices. </span>
</p></div></div></div></div></div><button type="button" style="visibility:visible" aria-label="Previous" class="pf-slider-prev none hide"></button><button type="button" style="visibility:visible" aria-label="Next" class="pf-slider-next none hide"></button></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-e037" data-category="Collection Suggestion" data-name="Tea" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-eGPXGI loUizX pf-16_ pf-color-scheme-1"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-bilyIR cCHonK"><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-17_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-dkYRCH jKtCIg pf-18_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hOGkXu fXbcZH pf-19_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key facts and statistics</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-dVNjXY jGYlKM pf-21_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-jHkVzv iFnjrD pf-22_ pf-text-1">According to the General Dental Council (GDC), dental professionals are required to undertake a minimum of 100 hours of CPD over a five-year cycle, of which at least 50 hours must be verifiable.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-jHkVzv iFnjrD pf-24_ pf-text-1">A British Dental Association (BDA) survey found that 82% of dental professionals believe that CPD is essential for maintaining competence and keeping abreast of advancements in the field.






























































</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-jHkVzv iFnjrD pf-26_ pf-text-1">The Dental Protection Society highlights that 70% of dental negligence claims are related to failures in communication and record-keeping, underlining the importance of ongoing training in these areas.































































</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-28_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-dkYRCH jKtCIg pf-29_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hOGkXu fXbcZH pf-30_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key definitions
</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-dVNjXY jGYlKM pf-32_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-jHkVzv iFnjrD pf-33_ pf-text-1"><strong></strong><strong>Continuous Professional Development (CPD)</strong> - The ongoing learning, development, and reflection process to maintain and enhance professional competence.&nbsp;</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-jHkVzv iFnjrD pf-35_ pf-text-1"><strong>Enhanced CPD</strong> - A structured approach to CPD that emphasises reflective practice, peer learning, and outcomes-focused learning activities.





























































</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-37_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-dkYRCH jKtCIg pf-38_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hOGkXu fXbcZH pf-39_ pf-heading-1-h3">Relevant legislation, regulations, and best practice</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-dVNjXY jGYlKM pf-41_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-jHkVzv iFnjrD pf-42_ pf-text-1">The General Dental Council (GDC) sets the regulatory framework for CPD requirements for dental professionals in the UK.&nbsp;</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-jHkVzv iFnjrD pf-44_ pf-text-1">The GDC's Enhanced CPD scheme, introduced in 2018, emphasises the importance of reflective practice, peer feedback, and learning outcomes.






























































</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-jHkVzv iFnjrD pf-46_ pf-text-1">Best practice in enhanced CPD involves a blend of formal learning activities, such as courses and conferences, alongside informal learning through case discussions, audits, and reflective journals.
































































</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-48_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-dkYRCH jKtCIg pf-49_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hOGkXu fXbcZH pf-50_ pf-heading-1-h3">Understanding enhanced CPD</h3><p class="sc-dtMgUX eyUPwo pf-52_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Enhanced CPD transcends traditional notions of ticking boxes and accumulating hours. It embodies a holistic approach to professional development, integrating reflective practice and meaningful learning outcomes. Dental professionals are encouraged to engage in diverse learning activities tailored to their individual needs and areas for improvement.



</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-54_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-dkYRCH jKtCIg pf-55_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hOGkXu fXbcZH pf-56_ pf-heading-1-h3">Navigating the regulatory landscape</h3><p class="sc-dtMgUX eyUPwo pf-58_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The GDC's Enhanced CPD scheme outlines clear guidelines for dental professionals to adhere to. The framework provides a roadmap for effective CPD planning and implementation, from setting objectives to documenting learning outcomes. Compliance with these regulations is not just a legal requirement but a professional obligation to ensure the highest standards of patient care.



</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-60_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-dkYRCH jKtCIg pf-61_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hOGkXu fXbcZH pf-62_ pf-heading-1-h3">Embracing reflective practice</h3><p class="sc-dtMgUX eyUPwo pf-64_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">At the heart of enhanced CPD lies reflective practice, enabling dental professionals to evaluate their experiences and learn from them critically. Regular reflection on clinical cases, patient interactions, and professional challenges fosters continuous improvement and enhances clinical decision-making skills.




</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-66_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-dkYRCH jKtCIg pf-67_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hOGkXu fXbcZH pf-68_ pf-heading-1-h3">Harnessing technology for learning</h3><p class="sc-dtMgUX eyUPwo pf-70_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">In the digital age, technology plays a pivotal role in facilitating learning and knowledge dissemination. Online platforms, webinars, and e-learning modules offer convenient and flexible avenues for dental professionals to engage in CPD activities, irrespective of geographical constraints.





</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-72_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-dkYRCH jKtCIg pf-73_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hOGkXu fXbcZH pf-74_ pf-heading-1-h3">Recommendations
</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-dVNjXY jGYlKM pf-76_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-jHkVzv iFnjrD pf-77_ pf-text-1"><strong></strong><strong></strong>Develop a personalised CPD plan tailored to your professional goals and learning needs.&nbsp;</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-jHkVzv iFnjrD pf-79_ pf-text-1">To enrich your CPD experience, embrace a variety of learning modalities, including online courses, workshops, and peer discussions.






























































</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-jHkVzv iFnjrD pf-81_ pf-text-1">Cultivate a peer learning and collaboration culture within your dental team, fostering a supportive environment for continuous improvement.
































































